    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2662" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕδρη</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑδ</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">seat, stool</span> (see cut 33;
          also 75), <i><span class="en">Il. 19.77</span></i>; pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕδραι</span>, rows of <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">seats</span>, e. g.
          stone benches in the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγορά</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 8.16</span></i>; and elsewhere, e. g. <i><span class="en">Od. 3.7</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; τίειν ἕδρῃ</span>, honor ‘with a seat,’ i.
          e. show to a place of honor.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
